---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Elasticsearch Inverted Index & Search"
  description="Interactive visualization of Elasticsearch's inverted index, analyzer pipeline, Lucene segments, shards & replicas, and BM25 relevance scoring"
  breadcrumbs={[
    { label: "Home", href: "/" },
    { label: "Elasticsearch", href: "/elasticsearch/" },
    { label: "Inverted Index", href: "/elasticsearch/inverted-index/" }
  ]}
>
<div class="viz-container">
  <header class="viz-header">
    <h1>🔍 Inverted Index & Search</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">How Elasticsearch Indexes Documents and Finds Matches</p>
  </header>

  <!-- Overview -->
  <section class="overview-section">
    <div class="overview-card">
      <p>
        Elasticsearch stores data using <strong>inverted indexes</strong> — a mapping from every unique
        <em>term</em> to the list of <em>document IDs</em> that contain it (the <strong>posting list</strong>).
        Before indexing, text passes through an <strong>analyzer pipeline</strong>: character filters → tokenizer → token filters
        (lowercase, stemming, stop words). Documents are stored in immutable <strong>Lucene segments</strong> that are
        periodically merged. An index is split into <strong>shards</strong> distributed across the cluster,
        each with optional <strong>replicas</strong> for fault tolerance. Search queries fan out to all shards,
        and results are merged using <strong>BM25 relevance scoring</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 1. Analyzer Pipeline -->
  <section class="flow-section">
    <h2>🔬 Analyzer Pipeline</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">Type text to see how Elasticsearch breaks it into tokens through character filters, tokenizer, and token filters.</p>

    <div class="calculator-container">
      <div class="calc-input-row">
        <input type="text" id="analyzerInput" placeholder="Type text to analyze (e.g. 'The Quick Brown Foxes jumped!')" class="key-input" autocomplete="off" value="The Quick Brown Foxes jumped over lazy Dogs!">
        <button id="analyzeBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">Analyze</button>
      </div>

      <div class="pipeline-stages" id="pipelineStages"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Analyzer Explainer -->
  <section class="explain-section">
    <div class="explain-grid">
      <div class="explain-card">
        <h3>📝 Character Filters</h3>
        <p>
          Run <strong>before</strong> tokenization. Strip HTML tags, convert characters
          (e.g., <code>&amp;</code> → <code>and</code>), or apply regex replacements.
          The text is still a single string at this stage.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="explain-card">
        <h3>✂️ Tokenizer</h3>
        <p>
          Splits the character stream into individual <strong>tokens</strong>. The <em>standard tokenizer</em>
          splits on whitespace and punctuation. Other tokenizers include <code>keyword</code> (entire string as one token),
          <code>pattern</code>, and <code>ngram</code>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="explain-card">
        <h3>🔧 Token Filters</h3>
        <p>
          Transform tokens: <strong>lowercase</strong>, remove <em>stop words</em> (the, is, at),
          apply <strong>stemming</strong> (running → run, foxes → fox). Multiple filters
          can be chained. Order matters.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 2. Interactive Inverted Index Builder -->
  <section class="flow-section">
    <h2>📚 Build an Inverted Index</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">Add documents to see the inverted index grow. Each term maps to a posting list of document IDs.</p>

    <div class="calculator-container">
      <div class="calc-input-row">
        <input type="text" id="docInput" placeholder="Enter document text" class="key-input" autocomplete="off">
        <button id="addDocBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">+ Add Doc</button>
        <button id="resetIndexBtn" class="action-btn reset-btn">🔄 Reset</button>
      </div>
      <div class="preset-docs">
        <span class="preset-label">Quick add:</span>
        <button class="preset-btn" data-text="the quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog">fox & dog</button>
        <button class="preset-btn" data-text="elasticsearch is a distributed search engine">search engine</button>
        <button class="preset-btn" data-text="the fox is quick and clever">clever fox</button>
        <button class="preset-btn" data-text="distributed systems require careful design">distributed systems</button>
        <button class="preset-btn" data-text="search engines index documents for fast retrieval">indexing docs</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="index-display">
      <div class="docs-panel">
        <h3>📄 Documents</h3>
        <div id="docsList" class="docs-list"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="index-panel">
        <h3>📇 Inverted Index</h3>
        <div id="invertedIndex" class="inverted-index-table"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 3. Interactive Search -->
  <section class="flow-section">
    <h2>🔎 Search the Index</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">Search your indexed documents. See which docs match, which terms hit, and why they rank the way they do.</p>

    <div class="calculator-container">
      <div class="calc-input-row">
        <input type="text" id="searchInput" placeholder="Search query (e.g. 'quick fox')" class="key-input" autocomplete="off">
        <button id="searchBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">🔍 Search</button>
      </div>
      <div id="searchResults" class="search-results"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 4. BM25 Scoring -->
  <section class="flow-section">
    <h2>📊 BM25 Relevance Scoring</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">Adjust parameters to see how BM25 calculates relevance. Higher scores = more relevant.</p>

    <div class="flow-controls">
      <div class="slider-group">
        <label>k1 (term saturation): <strong id="k1Label">1.2</strong></label>
        <input type="range" id="k1Slider" min="0" max="30" value="12" class="slot-slider">
      </div>
      <div class="slider-group">
        <label>b (length normalization): <strong id="bLabel">0.75</strong></label>
        <input type="range" id="bSlider" min="0" max="100" value="75" class="slot-slider">
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bm25-interactive">
      <div class="bm25-params">
        <div class="slider-group vertical">
          <label>Term Frequency (tf): <strong id="tfLabel">3</strong></label>
          <input type="range" id="tfSlider" min="0" max="20" value="3" class="slot-slider">
        </div>
        <div class="slider-group vertical">
          <label>Doc Length: <strong id="dlLabel">100</strong></label>
          <input type="range" id="dlSlider" min="10" max="500" value="100" class="slot-slider">
        </div>
        <div class="slider-group vertical">
          <label>Avg Doc Length: <strong id="avgdlLabel">120</strong></label>
          <input type="range" id="avgdlSlider" min="10" max="500" value="120" class="slot-slider">
        </div>
        <div class="slider-group vertical">
          <label>Total Docs (N): <strong id="nLabel">1000</strong></label>
          <input type="range" id="nSlider" min="10" max="10000" value="1000" class="slot-slider">
        </div>
        <div class="slider-group vertical">
          <label>Docs with term (df): <strong id="dfLabel">50</strong></label>
          <input type="range" id="dfSlider" min="1" max="5000" value="50" class="slot-slider">
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bm25-output" id="bm25Output"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BM25 Explainer -->
  <section class="explain-section">
    <div class="explain-card highlight-card">
      <h3>💡 BM25 vs TF-IDF</h3>
      <p>
        Classic <strong>TF-IDF</strong> increases linearly with term frequency — a term appearing 10x scores 10x
        higher. <em>BM25</em> adds <strong>saturation</strong>: after a point, more occurrences barely increase the
        score (controlled by <code>k1</code>). The <code>b</code> parameter controls <strong>length normalization</strong> —
        longer documents are penalized because they naturally contain more terms. BM25 is Elasticsearch's
        <em>default scoring function</em> since version 5.0.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 5. Lucene Segments -->
  <section class="flow-section">
    <h2>📦 Lucene Segments</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">Documents are written to immutable segments. Watch segments accumulate and merge.</p>

    <div class="flow-controls">
      <button id="addSegmentBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">+ Write Segment</button>
      <button id="mergeSegmentsBtn" class="action-btn step-btn" disabled>🔀 Force Merge</button>
      <button id="resetSegmentsBtn" class="action-btn reset-btn">🔄 Reset</button>
    </div>

    <div class="flow-status" id="segmentStatus">
      <span class="status-badge idle" id="segmentBadge">Ready</span>
      <span class="status-text" id="segmentStatusText">Add segments to see how Lucene manages immutable data</span>
    </div>

    <div class="topology-container">
      <canvas id="segmentCanvas" width="820" height="320"></canvas>
    </div>

    <div class="failover-timeline" id="segmentTimeline"></div>
  </section>

  <!-- Segment Explainer -->
  <section class="explain-section">
    <div class="explain-grid">
      <div class="explain-card">
        <h3>📝 Immutable Segments</h3>
        <p>
          Each <strong>refresh</strong> (default 1s) creates a new segment from the in-memory buffer.
          Segments are <em>immutable</em> — once written, they never change. Deletes are tracked in
          a separate <code>.del</code> file. This immutability enables lock-free reads and OS-level caching.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="explain-card">
        <h3>🔀 Segment Merging</h3>
        <p>
          Too many small segments hurt performance. Lucene's <strong>merge policy</strong> (TieredMergePolicy)
          periodically combines small segments into larger ones, physically removing deleted documents.
          <code>force merge</code> reduces to a target number of segments (useful for read-heavy, static indexes).
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 6. Shards & Replicas -->
  <section class="flow-section">
    <h2>🌐 Shards & Replicas</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">See how a search query fans out across primary shards and results are merged by the coordinating node.</p>

    <div class="flow-controls">
      <div class="slider-group">
        <label>Primary Shards: <strong id="shardCountLabel">3</strong></label>
        <input type="range" id="shardSlider" min="1" max="6" value="3" class="slot-slider">
      </div>
      <div class="slider-group">
        <label>Replicas: <strong id="replicaCountLabel">1</strong></label>
        <input type="range" id="replicaSlider" min="0" max="2" value="1" class="slot-slider">
      </div>
      <button id="runQueryBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">🔍 Run Query</button>
      <button id="resetShardsBtn" class="action-btn reset-btn">🔄 Reset</button>
    </div>

    <div class="flow-status" id="shardStatus">
      <span class="status-badge idle" id="shardBadge">Ready</span>
      <span class="status-text" id="shardStatusText">Configure shards and run a distributed query</span>
    </div>

    <div class="topology-container">
      <canvas id="shardCanvas" width="820" height="400"></canvas>
    </div>

    <div class="failover-timeline" id="shardTimeline"></div>
  </section>

  <!-- Shard Explainer -->
  <section class="explain-section">
    <div class="explain-grid">
      <div class="explain-card">
        <h3>📨 Query Phase (Scatter)</h3>
        <p>
          The coordinating node sends the query to <strong>one copy</strong> of each shard (primary or replica).
          Each shard executes the query locally and returns a <em>priority queue</em> of
          <code>(doc_id, score)</code> pairs — just IDs and scores, not full documents.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="explain-card">
        <h3>📋 Fetch Phase (Gather)</h3>
        <p>
          The coordinator <strong>merges</strong> all shard results, picks the global top-N,
          then fetches the actual documents from the relevant shards. This two-phase approach
          minimizes data transfer — only the winning documents are fetched in full.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="viz-footer">
    <p>Based on <a href="https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/index.html" target="_blank">Elasticsearch Documentation</a> and <a href="https://lucene.apache.org/" target="_blank">Apache Lucene</a></p>
  </footer>

  <div class="share-buttons">
    <span>Share this visualization:</span>
    <a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Interactive%20visualization%20of%20Elasticsearch%20inverted%20index%20and%20BM25%20scoring&url=https://systeminternals.dev/elasticsearch/inverted-index/" target="_blank" class="share-btn">𝕏 Twitter</a>
    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=https://systeminternals.dev/elasticsearch/inverted-index/" target="_blank" class="share-btn">in LinkedIn</a>
    <a href="https://news.ycombinator.com/submitlink?u=https://systeminternals.dev/elasticsearch/inverted-index/&t=Interactive%20Elasticsearch%20Inverted%20Index%20%26%20BM25%20Scoring%20Visualizer" target="_blank" class="share-btn">🟧 Hacker News</a>
  </div>
</div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .viz-container {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .viz-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .viz-header h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, #00d4ff, #60a5fa, #a855f7);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .subtitle {
    color: #888;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .section-desc {
    color: #888;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  /* Overview */
  .overview-section {
    margin-bottom: 50px;
  }

  .overview-card {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1), rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.05));
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.3);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 24px 28px;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #ccc;
  }

  .overview-card strong { color: #fff; }
  .overview-card em { color: #00d4ff; font-style: normal; font-weight: 500; }

  /* Action Buttons */
  .action-btn {
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 10px;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .action-btn:disabled {
    opacity: 0.4;
    cursor: not-allowed;
  }

  .primary-btn {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00d4ff, #0099cc);
    color: white;
  }

  .primary-btn:hover:not(:disabled) {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 5px 20px rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.4);
  }

  .step-btn {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #a855f7, #7c3aed);
    color: white;
  }

  .step-btn:hover:not(:disabled) {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 5px 20px rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.4);
  }

  .reset-btn {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    color: #aaa;
  }

  .reset-btn:hover { background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2); color: #fff; }

  /* Flow Section */
  .flow-section {
    margin-bottom: 50px;
  }

  .flow-controls {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .flow-status {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    border-radius: 10px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
  }

  .status-badge {
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .status-badge.idle { background: rgba(107, 114, 128, 0.3); color: #9ca3af; }
  .status-badge.searching { background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.2); color: #00d4ff; }
  .status-badge.merging { background: rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.2); color: #a855f7; }
  .status-badge.done { background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.2); color: #60a5fa; }
  .status-badge.writing { background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.2); color: #22c55e; }
  .status-badge.scatter { background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.2); color: #00d4ff; }
  .status-badge.gather { background: rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.2); color: #a855f7; }

  .status-text {
    color: #aaa;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  /* Calculator */
  .calculator-container {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 24px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .calc-input-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .key-input {
    flex: 1;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
    color: #fff;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-family: 'Monaco', 'Menlo', monospace;
    outline: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .key-input:focus {
    border-color: #00d4ff;
  }

  .key-input::placeholder {
    color: #555;
  }

  /* Pipeline Stages */
  .pipeline-stages {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
  }

  :global(.stage) {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 16px;
  }

  :global(.stage-header) {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }

  :global(.stage-arrow) {
    text-align: center;
    color: #555;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
  }

  :global(.token-list) {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px;
  }

  :global(.token-chip) {
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-family: 'Monaco', 'Menlo', monospace;
  }

  :global(.token-chip.original) {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    color: #ccc;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
  }

  :global(.token-chip.filtered) {
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1);
    color: #00d4ff;
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.3);
  }

  :global(.token-chip.removed) {
    background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.1);
    color: #ef4444;
    border: 1px solid rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.3);
    text-decoration: line-through;
  }

  :global(.token-chip.stemmed) {
    background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.1);
    color: #22c55e;
    border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.3);
  }

  /* Presets */
  .preset-docs {
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .preset-label {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #666;
  }

  .preset-btn {
    padding: 6px 14px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
    color: #aaa;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .preset-btn:hover {
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1);
    border-color: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.3);
    color: #00d4ff;
  }

  /* Index Display */
  .index-display {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 20px;
  }

  .docs-panel, .index-panel {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 20px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
  }

  .docs-panel h3, .index-panel h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  :global(.doc-item) {
    padding: 10px 14px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #ccc;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  :global(.doc-item.highlight) {
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1);
    border-color: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.3);
  }

  :global(.doc-id) {
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    margin-right: 8px;
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.15);
    color: #00d4ff;
  }

  :global(.index-row) {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    padding: 8px 12px;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    transition: all 0.2s;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  :global(.index-row:hover) {
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.05);
    border-color: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.2);
  }

  :global(.index-row.highlight) {
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1);
    border-color: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.3);
  }

  :global(.term-name) {
    font-family: 'Monaco', 'Menlo', monospace;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #00d4ff;
    min-width: 80px;
  }

  :global(.term-arrow) {
    color: #555;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }

  :global(.posting-list) {
    display: flex;
    gap: 4px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  :global(.posting-id) {
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.15);
    color: #a855f7;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  :global(.posting-id.match) {
    background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.2);
    color: #22c55e;
  }

  :global(.term-freq) {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: #666;
    margin-left: auto;
  }

  /* Search Results */
  .search-results {
    min-height: 40px;
  }

  :global(.search-hit) {
    padding: 14px 18px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    animation: eventAppear 0.3s ease-out;
  }

  :global(.hit-header) {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  :global(.hit-score) {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.15);
